    {
      "type": "note",
      "id": "note--89c0d1e2-f3a4-b5c6-d7e8-f90112233445",
      "spec_version": "2.1",
      "created": "2026-04-29T10:52:00.000Z",
      "modified": "2026-04-29T10:52:00.000Z",
      "abstract": "KB C2 Investigation Notes",
      "content": "Panel is live on port 4000 with JWT-authenticated API. Stage payload (/api/stage) is served without authentication (11.5MB encrypted binary). Ports 8443, 8888, 9090, 9999 reported by Shodan but not responding at time of investigation. Ukrainian-targeting phishing campaign with templates for PrivatBank, Ukrposhta, DPS, and Diia. Default SMTP via smtp.ukr.net suggests Ukrainian email infrastructure compromise. Monero mining via pool.hashvault.pro.",
